Settings:
    [ ] Always Flush
        After a pass iterates over a monster, write it to disk and forget about it.
        This means the data will not be stored in memory until the final related pass, but this also means a lot more writing to disk and checking diffs.
    [ ] Export to Mod
        Solves the replay issue and makes it easier to share with others.
        After generation, prompt the user to reload mods.
        Include the configuration inside the folder as well.
    [ ] Spoiler Logging
        That is, noting down every single change in one really massive file for users to look through.